      • BDEF_OBJECT

        @Deprecated
public final RDFName BDEF_OBJECT
        Deprecated. 
        Behavior Definition Object, in pre-3.0 terminology.

        In 3.0, an objects "typeness" is determined by its content model. What used to be known as BDef objects in Fedora 2.x are analogous to objects in the Models.SERVICE_DEFINITION_3_0 model in Fedora 3.0.

      • BMECH_OBJECT

        @Deprecated
public final RDFName BMECH_OBJECT
        Deprecated. 
        Behavior Mechanism Object, in pre-3.0 terminology.

        In 3.0, an objects "typeness" is determined by its content model. What used to be known as BMech objects in Fedora 2.x are analogous to objects in the Models.SERVICE_DEPLOYMENT_3_0 model in Fedora 3.0.

      • DATA_OBJECT

        @Deprecated
public final RDFName DATA_OBJECT
        Deprecated. 
        Data Object, in pre-3.0 terminology.

        In 3.0, an objects "typeness" is determined by its content model. What used to be known as data objects in Fedora 2.x are analogous to objects in the Models.FEDORA_OBJECT_3_0 model in Fedora 3.0.
